&lt;h1&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specialty Doctor in Urology&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Urology Department are looking for an enthusiastic, forward-thinking Specialty Doctor in Urology Surgery to join the team substantively.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We want to invest in applicants who are motivated and dedicated to providing high standards of patient care and see their own personal and professional development as a priority but who will be fit to manage the growing challenges of healthcare in the UK as we move forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have two hospital sites. Both have fully equipped theatre facilities. Acute and emergency theatre cases are undertaken on our ‘hot’ site Warrington hospital, with day case work being done at Halton site. Outpatient’s clinics are provided at both hospitals. There is an Endoscopy Unit on both sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the applicant has specific competencies or interests in sub-specialty areas, this will be supported.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full details are included in the supplementary information pack.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested applicants are invited to contact Mrs Kirsty Overend, CBU Senior Assistant Manager on 01925 665013 or k.overend@nhs.net to organise an informal visit.&lt;/p&gt;
